metadata.name: Glomularus #33
metadata.description:
Glomularus is an exploration in generative, artificial life forms. The project is an extension of my Protobyte series, begun in 2004.

Driven by Verlet icosahedra and responsive tendrils, Glomulari live in a spherical virtual ecosystem (V-eco) enhanced through user interaction.

Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
  drag -> camera rotation
  drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
  scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
  1-9: add acceleration
  -, +: reduce | increase V-eco sphere radius
  f, g: reduce | increase fog
  p: screen capture

Tip:
To decrease creature acceleration, reduce V-eco sphere radius

Note:
Please post your favorite Glomularus screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

metadata.name: Metropolis IX #164
metadata.description:
We divide spaces into smaller spaces which we conquer and live in our solitude. We call that Metropolis.

Started this piece as a rule based generative art. Simply the algorithm takes a rectangle and throws 2 random points inside it within defined x and y distances. Then using those 2 points, algorithm draws another rectangle and assigns letters to the corners of rectangle "A,B,C,D" starting from top left corner in clockwise direction. Then it starts to draw cells from inner rectangle's corner A to parent's corner A and goes on. Once 4 cells are created, it creates 4 more cells in between other cells, thus dividing a rectangle into 9 pieces. This is where "IX" comes from. Depending on the cell properties; algorithm assigns circles, triangles, lines and points to cells creating a city scape when certain parameters are given to the division algorithm.

There are 18 possible outcomes:
"Hazy Day" 13% probability (half of this style will come with slightly more color transition)
"Hazy Night" 10% probability
"Crystal Day" 11% probability
"Crystal Night" 5% probability
"Mondrian Day"  3% probability
"Mondrian Night" 3% probability
"Bauhaus Day" 3% probability
"Bauhaus Night" 3% probability
"1 Chroma Day" 4% probability (Multiple values of a single hue on a monochrome gradient)
"Mondrian Crystal Day" 3% probability
"Mondrian Crystal Night" 3% probability
"Monochrome Day" 3% probability 
"Monochrome Night" 4% probability 
"Vibrant Day" 12% probability
"Vibrant Night" 9% probability
"Rainbow Day' 5% probability
"Rainbow Night' 3% probability
"Chaotic Day"   3% probability (which takes pretty random parameters and 25% of this outcome has probability of creating very first coloring style of the project, see console for the hidden feature)




Press "1" to download 1000px height PNG
Press "2" to download 2000px height PNG
Press "3" to download 3000px height PNG
Press "4" to download 4000px height PNG
Press "5" to download 5000px height PNG
Press "6" to download 6000px height PNG
Press "7" to download 7000px height PNG
Press "8" to download 8000px height PNG
Press "9" to download 12000px height PNG
Press "m' to download 900x1600px PNG for mobile wallpaper

Use CTRL+SHIFT+C or CMD+SHIFT+C to open console for hidden features

Created from scratch with p5.js 
Murat Atimtay 2022 | @atimtay | www.muratatimtay.com

metadata.name: Paper Planes #241
metadata.description:
The joys of childhood are too easily forgotten. Paper Planes is a generative art collection celebrating the joy and magic of origami: from the simplest materials spring delightful forms brimming with ingenuity.

In homage to the handicraft of paper folding, we developed a collection of four pens each with a unique hand-drawn feel: Ink, Pencil, Gel and Dip. They ensure each of our ten origami birds are sketched with subtle imperfections.

Many of the birds are folded from patterned paper based on three traditional Japanese patterns: Seigaiha, Kōjitsunagi and Shippō. Other birds are crafted from block coloured paper which provides pop and contrast whilst sometimes birds match their background, accentuating the hand-drawn strokes that sketched them.

A range of layouts bring each mint to life. Birds can flock and fly across the page. They can be confined to a regimented grid or they can escape and embrace the chaos of the currents. Contrasting frames and borders highlight different colours within each of the 15 handcrafted palettes.

If you're feeling mischievous you can press 'C' in live view to ruffle some feathers…

https://www.phaust.art/paper-planes

----------

In live view, press 'S' to save a high resolution download or add '&size=#' to the end of the URL to render at a custom height.

Original artwork by Phaust. Spring 2022. London / Brighton. Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Rain Ritual #176
metadata.description:
Every windy gust.... every breeze, gave the restless grasses a chance to spread their suggestive rumours, their spurious gossip. All the while, Old Ones of the field towered above, chanting to their wrathful Sky God for more rain.... Always more rain. 

Instructions 
Intended for high resolutions. Use the following keys once render is complete, to export (letters export without a border) 

Square mode 
   1 (q) : 2048x2048  
   2 (w) : 3072x3072 
   3 (e) : 4096x4096 
   4 (r) : 5120x5120 

Landscape mode (increases spacing between objects to preserve aspect ratio) 
   5 (t) : 2560x1440 
   6 (y) : 3840x2160 
   7 (u) : 5128x2880 
   8 (I) : 7680x4320 

Note: Generated textures are resolution dependant, resulting in very slight differences across resolutions. Composition however, remains identical. 

Browsers 
Tested with Chrome, Edge and Firefox on Windows, Chrome on Mac. 
Note for Firefox users : Ensure "Use hardware acceleration" is ticked – Found in Settings / Performance. Other advanced settings to enable include : gfx.canvas.accelerated,  gfx.direct2d.force-enabled and gfx.offscreencanvas.enabled - Unfortunately even with these, Firefox appears slower than other browsers.  

Shoulders of Giants [license text and links included in source] 
- Aristid Lindenmayer – Formal L-System language (Tree routine) 
- P5.js - Creative coding framework 
- JS Topology Suite "JSTS", a port of Java Topology Suite "JTS" - High-level Geometry library 

Additional JS functions 
- Epistemex - Cardinal Splines library (Curve calculations) 
- MaetDol - K-Means library (Tree foliage routine) 
- Angelos Chalaris - Directed Graphs Tutorial (Tree routine)

metadata.name: Morning Mist #208
Love #255
metadata.description:
We all experience love at different scales, ranging from scarcely perceived instances of kindness to unforgettable affections shown to us by family and friends, pets and partners. Each of these moments link us to the same boundless and enveloping interconnectedness that persists across space and time: the infinite source of our deepest aspirations.

Like the feeling of simple bliss, ‘Love’ portrays the visceral radiant light and warmth of our innermost joys. By taking a moment to open ourselves up, these swirling worlds of weightless and seemingly infinite brush strokes invite us to slow down and dwell in prismatic intuitive swells.

In doing so, we may find the immense and omnipresent love that needs only our awareness to be felt.

__________

Press 1-9 to load at different scales (1 = 2,000x2,000 (default), 9 = 10,000x10,000)
When zoomed in, once the output is fully loaded, you can click and drag to move around the canvas
Press 'S' to save the image at the current scale
Press 'B' to toggle the background texture on or off
Press 'A' to toggle the loading animation (recommended for very large scales)

Created with p5.js
For third party license information, please see bundle.js.LICENSE.txt
__________
TENDER x teaboswell
May 2022

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #494
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.
